KAIZER Chiefs striker Bernard Parker has added another string to his bow by completing a Sports Management qualification from Boston City Campus and Business College. As the 33-year-old forward enters the twilight of his career he has already started preparing for life after football. Parkers Wife, Wendy Parker shared snaps of the players graduation on social media. "A dream doesn't become reality through magic; it takes sweat, determination and hard work. Success is no accident," Wendy wrote on instagram. "It is hard work, perseverance, learning, studying, sacrifice and most of all, love of what you are doing or learning to do. "There is no substitute for hard work, 23 or 24 hours a day. We are so proud of you Mr Parker." Wendy also revealed that Bernard scooped the top student award the class of 2019. 